# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-60137
# Product:   wordpress
# Tags:      [KEV] [RCE] [T1] [POC]
# Score:     120
# Tier:      CRITICAL — ACT NOW
# Generated: 2026-07-21T06:26:13.641517Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: PoC known — see [6] and [7]. Multiple public PoCs exist (19 known) [from
# PoC Availability context]. No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this
# pipeline — this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# Pattern basis: The vulnerability [1][3] is an unauthenticated SQL injection via the
# 'author__not_in' parameter in WP_Query, reachable through WordPress REST API and
# standard HTTP POST/GET requests. The match targets HTTP requests containing the
# 'author__not_in' parameter combined with common SQL injection payloads (UNION, SELECT,
# subquery syntax). Because no PCAP data is available and PoC source code was not
# directly parsed, the PCRE pattern is inferred from the CVE/advisory description and
# known SQL injection conventions for this parameter — NOT verified against actual
# exploit traffic.
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTE: The NVD CVSS score is 5.9 (MEDIUM) [1], however CISA has
# listed this CVE as ACTIVELY EXPLOITED IN THE WILD in the KEV catalog [2], and the
# priority assessment assigns a CRITICAL tier with RCE confirmed (AV:N/PR:N/UI:N).
# Analysts should weigh the KEV status and RCE vector heavily against the MEDIUM CVSS
# score — the score may not reflect current exploitation severity. Review both [1] and
# [2] before tuning thresholds.
#
# DRAFT — FOR ANALYST REVIEW BEFORE DEPLOYMENT. Tune pcre and threshold values
# for your environment. Consider testing in alert-only mode before enabling drop.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-60137 WordPress WP_Query author__not_in SQLi attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"GET"; nocase;
  http.uri; content:"author__not_in"; nocase;
  pcre:"/author__not_in\s*(?:%5B|\[)[^\]]*(?:UNION|SELECT|SLEEP|BENCHMARK|OR\s+1|AND\s+1|0x[0-9a-fA-F]|\-\-)/iU";
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 3, seconds 10;
  reference:cve,2026-60137;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev true, status experimental;
  classtype:web-application-attack; sid:9000101; rev:1; )

